<DOC><DOCNO> AP890610-0039 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-10-89 1228EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Greece-Clash     06-10 0170</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Greece-Clash,0175</SECOND><HEAD>40 Hurt In Clash Between Socialists and Conservative Youth Groups</HEAD><DATELINE>SALONICA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hundreds of youths preparing for giantpolitical rallies by Greece's two major political parties clashed inSalonica on Saturday, and police said at least 40 people wereinjured.   The clashes occurred before dawn as the youths belonging to thegoverning Panhellenic Socialist Movement and the conservative NewDemocracy Party were putting up posters in this northern city inpreparation for political rallies scheduled for Sunday and Mondaynight.   Both parties are reportedly busing in thousands of supporters ina show of strength for the crucial June 18 national elections.   Witnesses said the Socialist Movement youths destroyed two housetrailers and a campaign office used by the New Democrats.   New Democracy youths reportedly retaliated by smashing thewindows of a Socialist Movement campaign bureau and attacked theopposing youths with clubs.   It took riot police two hours to restore calm. Police said atleast 40 people were injured, most slightly, by clubs and stones.</TEXT></DOC>